{
  "id": "PYSEC-2026-208",
  "modified": "2026-06-13T10:45:05.285426528Z",
  "published": "2026-06-09T09:16:30.443Z",
  "aliases": [
    "CVE-2026-49818"
  ],
  "details": "The Apache Airflow Samba provider's `GCSToSambaOperator` joined GCS object names to the SMB destination path without a containment check, so an object named with `../` segments resolved a write path outside the configured `destination_path`. An attacker able to write objects into the source GCS bucket — typically an external data producer distinct from the trusted DAG author — could write files to arbitrary locations on the Samba target when the operator ran. Upgrade apache-airflow-providers-samba to 4.12.6 or later, which validates the resolved destination stays within `destination_path`.",
  "affected": [
